        "title": "fix(vllm): wire configured thinking params",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move vLLM Qwen thinking control to model-row `compat.thinkingFormat` only.\n- Stop reading Qwen thinking format from runtime params; legacy agent/provider params are handled by `openclaw doctor --fix` migration into `models.providers.vllm.models[].compat.thinkingFormat` or removed with an explicit manual-fix message when no concrete model can be inferred.\n- Preserve merged catalog compat so configured `thinkingFormat` does not drop discovered provider/model thinking metadata.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: vLLM Qwen thinking format is configured only on model metadata, with legacy param locations migrated or clearly removed by doctor.\nReal environment tested: local macOS checkout.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=120000 pnpm test src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-config-migrate.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/model-selection.test.ts --reporter verbose`; `OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=120000 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extensions.config.ts extensions/vllm/provider-policy-api.test.ts extensions/vllm/stream.test.ts extensions/vllm/provider-discovery.contract.test.ts --reporter verbose`; `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --stream-engine-output`.\nEvidence after fix: doctor and model-selection shards passed; vLLM extension shard passed; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings before the final conflict-free rebase, and the focused shards were rerun afterward on the pushed patch.\nObserved result after fix: configured Qwen models expose binary off/on thinking and request wrapping reads model compat only.\nWhat was not tested: live vLLM server.\n",
